cleaned_message: Also I've just received another letter from Ash and I would like to share it with you. Some good advice in there and I'm sure it will make you smile! When the agents of the state come knocking for you over some fabricated charges one of the weird things that strikes you is how serious they seem to take it. So back in May 22 there I was, in uniform about to drive into HMP Leeds to take a funeral escort out. About a mile from my home the blues and twos go on and I'm boxed in by 4 cop BMWs, 8 coppers armed with tasers and such jump out and do the thing. Eventually, after handcuffing me and treating me like I'm unexploded ordinance, they tell me that they say a rap video I shared on telegram contravened the counter terrorism act 2006. Off we go to Normanton police station, where I have to ask the cops to take my epaulettes with my rank and number off my shirt, what being in a jail with criminals and all. Eventually the interrogation begins. One lady cop who is in charge, and some fat mess bloke who despite being 30 looks half dead. Don't be fat, my dudes. They have real good poker faces while the fat mess reads me Mr Bond lyrics and then look at me meaningfully, like I'm supposed to start crying and confess how wrong I have been to share (inadvertently) a link to some rap tunes while calling for my homie Bond to be freed from Austrian prison. I remember him tripping over the line "abominable hominins" like 4 times, so I helped him out. He still couldn't get it right. When they interrogate you, you gotta be careful because they will try to trip you up. The lady cop asked me if I had been reckless when sharing the link, which I discovered later if I had agreed to would be a confession to terrorism, albeit a minor one. That would have been thrown in my face repeatedly at trial, and the trial was already gonna be a complete shit show. I really cannot stress it enough that you really should not talk to the cops unless you're very well lawyered up and know the law backwards. I guess then you could do some pretty fun games with em, but I'm not that smart so I'm a no comment kinda dude. Make no mistake these people love the expansion of the law. Rather than serving the public good, policing by consent, that shit is old news. Today these cops love the police state, and who wouldn't? dominating people and destroying them probably feels real good, if you serve Satan. Look out for the gleam in their eye, and if you see it tread careful because you're dealing with a bona fide government stooge who would holodomor you in an instant. Stay frosty Ash Political Prisoner, innit.

Good news my Nationalist fam! The system has confirmed that the family day for Ash is a GO! This means he will be reunited with his wonderful children for the first time in over 7 months! We can only imagine how emotional this will be. Plus of course on Saturday it's Ash's birthday, have you sent a card yet? I know some of you have already and Ash sends heartfelt thanks to you. Remember it's not too late to do so at: www.moonpig.co.uk Thank you fam!

Ash has sent another letter that would be good to share with you. Given that my sources of news are the Electric J and wireless radio I assume I know less about current events than if I relied on prophetic dreams, so anything I write to you about current evens can be considered speculative fiction about about an alternate dimension. Any similarities to circumstances spiritual or temporal is therefore purely coincidental. I don't know if I mentioned this before but in the current mileu of Mostly Peaceful Protesting the state is running on a hair trigger, arresting people for yelling hurty words at the constabulary and the like. There's basically no need to break stuff or commit any crime if your goal is to get arrested- We'll see if a man telling a crowd of people through a megaphone to go and slit the throats of his political opponents gets more jail time than a guy who ran a sports club and had bad digital hygiene. The overstep by the state is going to teach the right wing what the left learned a long time ago- diversity is good, when it's a diversity of tactics. People should google that. People should also realise that the police will track them through CCTV back to the point where they put on their union jack mask and then use the clothes they were wearing to tie them to crimes. If anyone has seen an anti capitalist protest before you'll see Black Bloc guys arriving in normal clothes and sometimes setting up umbrella shelters in the middle of a crowd to black up, or using some other method to hid their identities completely. People should know that you shouldn't wear anything to a protest that you don't mind binning. Obviously nobody I know would be dumb enough to go and do anything but peacefully advocate for their rights and group interests. There's loads of good advice on this kind of stuff on anarchist websites, if you are a communist or anarchist you can write what you want on the internet. They don't even stop you. Anyway, that's just what I think about this story that I'm writing about a country that isn't this one, some time in 1973. Stay out of jail. There's criminals in here, you know. God Bless, Ash (An actual, real life Political Prisoner)

cleaned_message: I don't know if you grew up a little weird and alienated, but I did and I'm glad I just had grunge to deal with rather than the internet. There but for the grace of God go I and any of you, feel blessed that your parents loved you and taught you right. In good conscience, after seeing WSAC stop one kid going over the edge without trying, I couldn't keep WSAC a secret. It's too cool. It's not like it's a stroke of genius or anything, we copied plenty of other active clubs around the world. Together though I still believe that the 3.0WN lifestyle is the path to fix our 'community', or at least show some kids that despair and rage isn't all that there is. Hope all you active club chaps are doing well, you're doing more for the future of our people than anybody else. Every rep is a little victory. So yeah, White Stag, an exercise in political jiu-jitsu (sometimes using real ju-jitsu) that the state loves to hate. The issue for me at least was I wasn't perfect enough. I screwed up and didn't read every pdf I downloaded. If I had read the damn thing, I'd have deleted it and be outside now- instead of being psychologically tortured in one of the most violent jails in England. Hey, it could be worse. I could be violently tortured in a prison full of psychologists, so there's always a sunny side, right? "And how did the thumbscrews make you feel about your relationship with your mother?"It's the small margins I guess is the point of all this. Small margins are how we make improvements to our minds and physiques. It's also how the powers that be will catch you, if you be slippin. Don't screw up like I did and give these scumbags an opening, because they hit like a truck when they land. It's always something weird to think about but really the state has entirely the wrong outlook on groups like WSAC if they actually cared about de-radicalisation or reducing 'terrorism'. We know they love it when young, disaffected youth go over the edge, because if they cared about stopping it the White Stag was their best friend. Alright, maybe not friend but you don't make peace with your friends, right? Instead of making peace, the government treats us like a pest to be eradicated, which is ironic considering the kind of propaganda they promote about our philosophical forebears. Maybe we have the wrong outlook too. Maybe more of us need to be in jail for wild lengths of time for mind-crimes, it's probably the best activism you can do. Don't do that though. Stay out of jail, it's really bad for your health and as you have read from this, I'm probably losing a bit of my mind in here. Anyway, that's all I really gotta say about WSAC for now. It was a lot of fun, we hurt nobody (except each other in the boxing ring) and helped lots of people. Hopefully the bar we set can be smashed by the next group and the group after that, and after that. Always keep your eyes on the horizon, towards the dawn, and our future. God bless you all.

Nothing positive happens, everyone stays mad on the internet. It might be just beyond my ability to understand, but I don't see how this helps. We also have our share of the autistic weirdo‚Äôs, alienated youth, freaks, geeks and flat out nutters. This is exactly the same as in other political scenes, except where communist groups can advocate for guillotining every politician, judge and banker in the land and nothing happens, nationalists go to prison. I'm not trying to minimise it or justify it, but it's the reality and nobody seemed to be doing anything about showing people 'we' are ostensibly aligned with or should at least care about that calling for or perpetrating violence isn't helping 'the movement'. We figured that if the FBI can set up fake groups like The Base and O9A and encourage young white lads to do terrorism, the least we could do is push back on that. The way to do that is go public, go loud, and stay jacked. It was highly effective. Naturally, Hope Not Hate went mental and sent an operative to infiltrate us. We bought him dinner and some beers, and in their annual 'State of Hate' Report for 2022 they could only really give us a positive write up. Subscriptions to the social media channels boomed, applications to join soared. Some other 'political' groups cried their little hearts out about possibly losing members to a tiny sports club, but in general everyone was just like Fonzie. What's Fonzie like? Cool, baby. Cool. The White Stag was doing good, we had by this point an experienced core group who were passing on skills to the younger/newer guys. It's important that young men learn how to box, because if you don't you don't have respect for violence. You can't control your impulses. It's important to learn about hiking, map reading and so on. It's good to shoot archery. All these things make men, better. Naturally, the security services shat bricks and started watching us like the proverbial hawk, except not as cool as hawks. Like nerds. Watching us like nerds. So I guess others on here have written about the day in May 2022 when I got arrested under terrorism laws for sharing a link to an archive of rap songs. Free Mr Bond, by the way. Hope he's alright. Suffice to say that day, unmarked cars, MI5, interrogations, fat cops being unable to read rap lyrics right, that day kicked off 2 years of Orwellian Nightmare, which is a totally over used term but I think I've got a good chance of winning the no-prize for having the state's boot stamped into my face forever, so I'm claiming it now. All the subsequent craziness, beating the rap music rap but getting jailed for a book it was shown in court it was illogical and impossible for me to have read, all that was really because the state (fuelled by Hysteria Not Hate) got scared by the aesthetics of a sports club. Here's the thing. Nobody in the state apparatus helps or wants to help nationalist youth stay clear of poison like O9A or AtomWaffen. The Shawcross review of Prevent and KC Kelly's report on terror offender management both scratch their heads as to why the state doesn't even engage with nationalist groups, why there's no creative thought in reaching the only demographic at risk of real radicalisation- men in their late teens, often autistic, often alienated from society. The state likes it when these lads go off the deep end, and for everyone else their line is you can either stop thinking the bad thoughts or go to prison if you do anything other than sit online making tedious videos. I'm not going to Bible bash you guys too much but Jesus is important to me and he said Be Excellent To Each Other. What we do in this country -in nationalist circles- is far from this. We do not look out for the weakest of us who are easy prey for evil men to turn into the 'evil neo nazi' stereotype. What do we do? Call them spergs and try to move on as quickly as possible.

You are plainly a very dangerous individual. The test established by section 308 is met. The public need to be protected from you for as long as possible. (My editing in bold and not Ash‚Äôs, to highlight the bias personal attack by the judge) ‚ÄùWhere do you even begin? I'm a National Socialist, not a Neo-Nazi, thanks. I'm not a white supremacist. WSAC isn't a white supremacist organisation, and I don't hate anyone. I am accused of having a clear motivation for terrorism, based on a book that I never read and wasn't modelling my life on, and no evidence to say I was interested in terrorism. If I was on a course of racist and hate-related violence, that's news to me, news to my family, and again based on nothing more than the WRM itself. Here's the logic. Judge Richardson said: You had the WRM. You therefore read it and absorbed all its messaging. You lived your life by it. Therefore, all evidence must be viewed through the lens of the WRM, and if the evidence doesn't fit the WRM theory, that's just not important. I also read Lord of The Rings but I don't believe I'm a sodding hobbit! What WSAC started out as was a group of nationalist guys who were disillusioned with politics, and people who like politics. It's no fun going for a beer with political dissidents, because everything is going badly and nobody has any solutions. The solution to this spiritual desert was a new philosophy. Screw politics, Hail push up! In the view of White Stag, how smart you are or how much you know about 1930s economic policy is irrelevant if you aren't able to hike 8 miles and then fight 3 rounds of boxing. If you are into nationalism and are sat in your bedroom on a weekend instead of climbing, hiking, lifting or running, you're doing it wrong. Anyway, for 18 months we operated in complete secrecy. Why secrecy? Because literal communists and the British Secret Police will definitely try to ruin your life, and there's no need to make it easy for them. The proto-Stag grew in numbers, had a lot of adventures, and did a lot of push ups. Some fell by the wayside; some people came on one hike and couldn't cut it. We realised that by virtue of our year being organised around 4 challenging, weighted, long distance hikes that this wasn't for entry level chaps. We began to recruit accordingly. Brotherhood was forming, not the fake kind that people speak about on the internet, but the real thing forged out of nearly dying on mountains in blizzards when the rest of the country was being told to hide under the bed from the China virus. We became brothers by being a bit crap at boxing and trying to get better by beheading each other in dive boxing gyms, rented when other classes weren't on. Some of us got jacked. Others lost some fat. Everyone had a fucking blast. Then a couple of things happened, pretty close together. I figured that remaining an anonymous group had a shelf life, and increased our potential risk if the feds discovered us. From personal experience it's hard enough defending an entirely legal athletics club against accusations from the state that your real intention is create an army of racist super soldiers, without them being able to cry "if you had nothing to hide why did you hide" as well. The second thing that happened was one of the guys confided in me that before joining us, he was in a dark place and was considering "doing something". Yeah, we probably know what that would have ended up like. He then said he didn't feel like that anymore. He said that was down to us. By accident, we had stumbled on how to de-radicalise nationalist youth. It was pretty clear to me at that point that WSAC was more than just a bunch of dudes lifting weights who had an interest in early 20th Century European politics. We have to accept that nationalism has a pretty poor reputation, and part of that reputation is absolutely down to the nationalist 'community' such as it is. In reality, the nationalist 'community' can be better described as disparate personality cults insulting each other and calling each other federal agents.

This is an open letter written by Ash a while ago. I thought it would be a good time to publish it so you can get an idea of how he is thinking. It is months old so recent events are obviously not mentioned. Hopefully more letters like this will follow, to keep you updated. So they said I live my life by the WRM... It's one of those things prosecutors throw out there to chum the water for the media. The problem is when we compare what the WRM says to do, to with what I did. Bear in mind also that the WRM was published in 2006 (coincidentally the same year that the law banning such material was passed in the UK) and said that unless there was all-out race war by 2016, it was all over. So that's also the first problem, everything that I'm about to relate to you is 8 years out of date at a minimum. If you're living your life by a book, you'd probably want it to have some timeless life lessons in it. The Bible is a good one for that. No sell by date. You should read The Bible. Note: I'm doing this from my memory of seeing this document in court, over a year ago. Any inaccuracies are my fault, but then again don't go downloading this crap to fact check me. It's a bad document. The WRM says that you have two ways to be a real white nationalist activist. You can be a mask off, nice guy NatSoc who publicly preaches peaceful means but in private you must (somehow) support terrorism. The other way to be an activist is to be a lone wolf assassin, obviously working in secrecy, and killing people like you're in a video game. I did neither of these things with White Stag. The group that was the precursor to White Stag was non-public facing, and as far as I know the establishment had no idea we existed. Now, if I had wanted to be a terrorist then it would make sense to keep your secret terrorist group, well, secret. Instead we went public once we realised that White Stag could have far-reaching benefits to many people, members and otherwise. So, we clearly weren't secret assassins, and in the two years since my arrest there has not been a spate of nationalist attacks carried out by my guys, so I think we can say that this wasn't the intent in the first place. WSAC was not a lone wolf assassin club. I also wasn't a public facing, nice guy nationalism guy. I was about to go public before my untimely arrest, but I was in the process of leaving the Prison Service and needed a couple of months. I was going to do this as being public facing is a protection against doxxing and other attacks. I am on public record through my writings at Republic Standard of disavowing violence for political purposes and all forms of racial bigotry. That's not nationalism, that's petty tribalism. There's no evidence of my advocating violence against anyone. You might think that after the police went through all my devices that there would surely be some kind of hint that, secretly, I was advocating terrorism. Not a single sentence, in thousands of messages. My speeches to the members of WSAC (maybe someone still has those somewhere) never advocate for violence except in terms of combat sports, for the benefit of the members. So, you can be assured I'm not following the WRM there, either. Even so, Judge Richardson said in his sentencing remarks: ‚ÄúThere is no doubt you hold deeply ingrained racist and homophobic views which are unshakeable. You are proud to be a neo-Nazi and white supremacist. You were in the process of recruiting white disaffected men to your white supremacist organisation and you had the clear motivation for terrorism targeting those whom you hated. The PSR (Pre Sentencing Report) makes it clear you pose significant dangers. I am of the view that you are unrepentant and have shown not the slightest remorse. I take the view you pose significant risks to society and public protection demands an enhanced level of protection. It is my view that unless you are monitored very closely you will continue upon the course of racist and other hate-related violence amounting to terrorism to which the WRM was directed.

It just so happens that a family open day falls almost on his birthday and his wife and children will fly over from Poland to be with him.
